main event: Three small white lights assembling a diamond in appearance were observed near Biggs AFB in Texas on July 3, 1960.
interesting points: The objects appeared to travel about 5,000 feet in elevation and then disappeared.
A white glowing moon-like appearance extended as the objects' trail disappeared.
The objects appeared to be operating, according to the observers.
The objects were observed for 5-10 seconds by military personnel, including sentries and dog handlers.
The investigating officer could not confirm the sighting and suggested the objects may have been a peculiar meteorite disintegration.
sighted object: three small white lights in a diamond formation
witnesses: military personnel, including sentries and dog handlers
